title: Massive crocodile taken to Steve Irwin’s Australia Zoo despite traditional owners’ anger over removal
summary: Old Faithful, a giant freshwater crocodile measuring over 4 meters, has been relocated to a facility on the Sunshine Coast. The crocodile was removed from a waterhole in far north Queensland due to safety concerns. The rehoming aims to ensure both the crocodile's well-being and public safety.

title: ‘History won’t forgive us’ if UK falls behind in quantum computing race, says Tony Blair
summary: Former Prime Minister William Hague has warned that the UK is falling short in high-risk capital and infrastructure necessary to leverage advancements in powerful technology. He emphasized that without these resources, the country may miss out on significant economic benefits. Hague's concerns highlight the need for strategic investments to support innovation and growth in the tech sector.
